title: Art at Auction - Year at Sotheby Parke Bernet 1974-75
description:
Art at Auction - The Year at Sotheby Parke Bernet, 1974-75
Viking Press | 1975 | ISBN: 0670134066 | English | 470 pages | PDF | 82.8 MB

Art at Auction presents a richly illustrated selection of the most interesting and significant works of art sold in the international salesrooms of Sotheby Parke Bernet during the season ending in July 1 975. This has been distinguished by the continuing expansion of overseas sales, including the first auction in Monte Carlo which totaled about $4-5 million, and the incorporation of the Dutchauctioneers Mak van Waay into the Sotheby Parke Bernet Group
